\f0\b\fs54 \cf0 Mango Sorbet
\fs44 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs30 \cf0 Yield: 1 1/2 quarts; 6 servings\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs46 \cf0 Ingredients
\f1\b0\fs42 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\fs44 \cf0 3/4 cup sugar\
5 large ripe mangoes, peeled and seeded\
1/4 cup freshly squeezed {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/orange/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 orange juice}}\
1/4 teaspoon kosher salt\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs46 \cf0 Directions
\f1\b0\fs44 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural
\cf0 Place the sugar and 1/2 cup water in a small {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/saucepan/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 saucepan}} and cook until the sugar dissolves. Set aside.\
Place the mangoes in a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/food-processor/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 food processor}} fitted with the steel blade and puree. You should have about 5 cups of mango. If you want a smoother sorbet, you can process the puree through a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/food-mill/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 food mill}} fitted with a medium blade.\
Combine the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/mango/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 mango}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/sugar-syrup/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 sugar syrup}}, orange juice, and salt and refrigerate until cold. Freeze in an ice cream machine according to the manufacturer's directions. (The sorbet will be soft.) Store in freezer.}